### ============================================================
### INSTRUMENT: Conflict Dynamics Profile (CDP) — Individual Form
### Developer: Capobianco, Davis & Whitman — Cloke Institute
### Format: Likert-scale items | Self-report (CDP-I) and 360-rater (CDP-360)
### Subscales: active_constructive, passive_constructive,
###            active_destructive, passive_destructive
### Level: Individual (self and rater perspectives)
### Admin time: 20–25 minutes (self); 15 min (each rater)
### ============================================================
###
### ⚠ NEW SCHEMA REQUIREMENTS FOR THIS INSTRUMENT:
###
###   "rater_type": "self" | "multi_rater"
###     The CDP exists in two parallel forms. The self-report (CDP-I) uses
###     first-person phrasing ("I..."). The 360 form (CDP-360) uses
###     third-person phrasing ("This person...") and is completed by
###     raters the subject nominates. Both forms use the same item IDs
###     but rater_type determines which phrasing template is served.
###
###   "behavior_temperature": "hot" | "cool"
###     CDP's unique structural feature. "Hot" behaviors are active and
###     escalating (e.g., Displaying Anger, Winning at All Costs).
###     "Cool" behaviors are passive or de-escalating (e.g., Avoiding,
###     Reflective Thinking). Combined with constructive/destructive axis,
###     this creates a 2x2 classification per item.
###
###   "behavior_cluster": string
###     CDP organizes items into named behavioral clusters within each
###     subscale. Clusters: "perspective_taking", "creating_solutions",
###     "expressing_emotions", "reaching_out", "reflective_thinking",
###     "delay_responding", "adapting", "winning_at_all_costs",
###     "displaying_anger", "demeaning_others", "retaliating",
###     "avoiding", "yielding", "hiding_emotions", "self_criticizing".
###
###   "rater_pool": { "min": 3, "max": 8, "role_types": [...] }
###     For CDP-360, specifies minimum raters needed for anonymity and
###     maximum raters accepted. Role types constrain which rater
###     categories the subject can nominate (peer, manager, direct_report).
###
###   "scale_range": { "min": 1, "max": 6, "labels": { ... } }
###     CDP uses a 6-point frequency scale (never → always),
###     not the standard 5-point. Must not collapse to 5-point.
###
### ============================================================

POST http://localhost:3030/api/surveys/templates
Content-Type: application/json
